In .NET 10 (and Android 11+), `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is deprecated at the platform level. The modern fix uses **Android window insets** to detect the keyboard height and apply bottom padding. Here's the approach:

## 1. Set your Activity to `AdjustResize` (still needed as a baseline)

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(... WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

## 2. Disable `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (it conflicts with chat layouts)

In `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(handlers =>
{
#if ANDROID
    Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();
#endif
});
```

## 3. Apply keyboard insets via a custom handler or platform code

Add a listener in your `MainActivity`:

```csharp
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Bottom padding = keyboard height (or nav bar if keyboard closed)
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
        v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight, bottom);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

## 4. XAML structure (simplified)

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" Placeholder="Type a message..." />
</Grid>
```

The insets listener adjusts the DecorView's bottom padding to match the keyboard height, pushing your entire layout up — effectively replicating the old `Resize` behavior using the modern WindowInsets API.

**On iOS**, `AdjustResize`-equivalent behavior is automatic. If you still see overlap, set `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` to stay connected (only disconnect it inside `#if ANDROID`).
